![](http://ootput.files.wordpress.com/2010/06/zsh.png?w=76 "zsh")

ZSH has a built-in function called `edit-command-line` which allows you to edit the current command with an external editor (defined by the environment variable `$EDITOR`). To enable this feature, add the following to your ZSH startup scripts:{% codeblock %}

autoload edit-command-line
zle -N edit-command-line
bindkey '^Xe' edit-command-line
{% endcodeblock %}


For the interested, [this](http://www.techrepublic.com/article/keyboard-shortcuts-in-bash-and-zsh/6178505) article lists some useful keyboard shortcuts in ZSH.